Why the Pittsburgh Steelers will win Super Bowl LVI

Steelers fans eating it up! (Bill Belecheck/AP)

Geoff Lowe | @GeoffALowe February 4, 2021, 12:19 PM
  • 37
Tom Brady @TomBrady July 8, 2021, 12:19 PM
  • 37

Ahead of Super Bowl LVI between the Pittsburgh Steelers and It Doesn't Matter, TB12 will break down why the Steelers will win the Lombardi Trophy this year.

Here we go!

It’s hard to add to a legacy when you’re already considered one of, The Greatest of All Time, but Ben Roethlisberger can do just that this year.

In search of the team's seventh Lombardi Trophy, #7 will head into retirement on top of the world!

A Super Bowl LVI win would be another remarkable accomplishment in a career full of them.

Standing in the way is Patrick Mahomes and myself, as formidable an opponent as there is in the NFL. We will just not be able to stand up to the Black and Gold this year.

The Steelers will, underdogs as they are, overcome the defending champions and KC. I know they’ll do just that.
